<unit id="19b901cd-e490-4998-8c79-241f3f8d2b9e">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 6</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>This add-on provides quick commands to manage objects on screen, including navigation and other possibilities.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="8a567dce-837d-4343-a603-cebf48e27fce">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 8</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Commands</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="c969c11d-623d-4dfa-90cf-2dd394c37d8a">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 10</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Control+NVDA+TAB: Steps through arrow key modes (see below for details).</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="7a883ee9-3487-4e6a-bc3e-3923249daf48">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 12</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Arrow key modes</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="72c59c0a-36b2-4712-bd21-ec4f0ffc93c3">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 14</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>The add-on provides four ways to use arrow keys:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="308a1d10-410d-4ed8-b246-649125d35408">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 16</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Classic (or normal mode): use arrow keys to move cursor.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="4db63059-9289-4251-a62d-ddf0fc551ea7">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 17</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Object nav: use arrow keys to move to next/previous/parent/first child objects.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="2a734881-46ee-4982-92b5-22ce0fe0850f">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 18</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Browse mode: use arrow keys to cycle through browse mode elements (web included) and move between them.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="59837278-abf2-471a-9c18-98fb09b61b1d">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 19</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Scan mode: use arrow keys to move through objects on screen regardless of hierarchy.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="aa7d48a8-b2ac-456c-81a1-514625b0b5b7">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 21</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>The following commands are available with arrow keys set to object nav:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="b2eb2264-dd8c-4477-8a69-6ad425297738">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 23</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Right arrow: next object.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="60dd2a9a-e30e-43fb-9e4b-191ca4708fd6">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 24</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Left arrow: previous object.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="e2d0fa38-828a-4177-b8d7-4b67909b3789">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 25</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Up arrow: parent object.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="d5870e94-c378-4bd7-b71b-2b13be156c05">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 26</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Down arrow: first child object.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="70c7c859-8a5d-4206-ac2c-ac6e451c56b9">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 27</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>SPACE or ENTER: activate.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
